casebody.data:
PEOPLE of the State of Michigan, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Henry Lee HENCE, Jr., Defendant-Appellant. SC: 158088
COA: 342023 Supreme Court of Michigan. April 30, 2019

Order

On order of the Court, the application for leave to appeal the June 21, 2018 order of the Court of Appeals is considered, and it is DENIED, because the defendant's motion for relief from judgment is prohibited by MCR 6.502(G). The motions to remand and for miscellaneous relief are DENIED.
